Libera tempore. Cn. Pompeius, by a law passed in his third consul- ship, defined the proportione of time to be allotted to the accuser and the accused respectively. The enactment was primarily to regulare the trial of Milo then about to take place, Ascon. Arg. Cic. pro Mil.
